<Base
  title="Quarry — native database manager for macOS"
  description="Quarry is a native macOS database manager for SQLite, SQLCipher, PostgreSQL, and MySQL."
>
  <img class="logo" src="/quarry-logo.svg" alt="Quarry app icon" />
  <h1>Quarry</h1>
  <p class="tagline">Professional database manager for macOS — native, fast, and encrypted-database ready.</p>

  <ul class="features">
    <li><strong>Open the databases you already use</strong>
        <span>Work with SQLite, SQLCipher, PostgreSQL, and MySQL from a native Mac app.</span></li>
    <li><strong>Review edits before they write</strong>
        <span>Inline editing, bulk changes, import, export, and SQL previews keep changes visible.</span></li>
    <li><strong>Search, compare, and maintain</strong>
        <span>Find data across tables, compare schemas or rows, and run integrity checks, vacuum, and backup tools.</span></li>
  </ul>

